# Implementation Plan: Projects Department Custom Approval Flow

Customizing the leave approval process for the **Projects** department to follow a specialized hierarchy: **HOD Projects → GM → CEO**, bypassing the Operations Manager (OM).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Role Definition**: I will formally add the `HOD_PROJECTS` role to the system. Users with this role will have the authority to perform the first-level approval for any employee in the "Projects" department.
> 
> **Dashboard Visibility**: The HOD Projects will receive a specialized dashboard view (similar to the OM) but restricted only to "Projects" department data.
> 
> **Rejection Logic**: If an HOD Projects rejects a request, it will terminate the flow immediately, identical to how OM rejection works today.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Backend Constants & Schema

#### [MODIFY] [constants.ts](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/server/src/utils/constants.ts)
- Add `HOD_PROJECTS: 'HOD_PROJECTS'` to `APP_CONSTANTS.ROLES`.

#### [MODIFY] [schema.prisma](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/server/prisma/schema.prisma)
- *Note*: No database migration is strictly required as status and role are strings, but I will add comments to the schema for documentation of the new `PENDING_HOD_PROJECTS` status.

